---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Getting Started" description="Get Voxeltron running in under 60 seconds.">
  <h1>Getting Started</h1>
  <p style="color: var(--color-text-2); font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 32px;">
    Voxeltron is a two-binary system: <code>voxeltrond</code> (the Rust daemon that runs on your server)
    and <code>voxeltron</code> (the Go TUI you use to manage it). This guide gets you from zero to a running deploy.
  </p>

  <div class="callout tip">
    <strong>No browser required.</strong> Voxeltron is managed entirely from your terminal via gRPC over TLS.
    Your web browser is not invited. It's for the best.
  </div>

  <h2>What you'll need</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>A Linux server (Debian/Ubuntu/Fedora/Arch — anything with Docker and systemd)</li>
    <li>Docker 24+ installed on the server</li>
    <li>A terminal on your local machine (macOS, Linux, or WSL2)</li>
    <li>Ports 80, 443, and 7443 open on the server firewall</li>
    <li>A domain name pointed at your server (for TLS)</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="callout info">
    Port 7443 is the gRPC management port. It never needs to be exposed publicly —
    you can tunnel it via SSH or put it behind a firewall. Port 80 and 443 are for your apps.
  </div>

  <h2>Quick Install</h2>

  <p>The fastest path: run the installer on your server.</p>

  <pre><code><span style="color: var(--color-teal);">$</span> curl -sSL https://voxeltron.dthink.ai/install.sh | bash</code></pre>

  <p>This installs both <code>voxeltrond</code> and <code>voxeltron</code> to <code>/usr/local/bin</code>.
  The installer detects your OS and pulls the correct binary.</p>

  <p>You can verify the install:</p>

  <pre><code><span style="color: var(--color-teal);">$</span> voxeltron --version
voxeltron v1.0.0 (go1.22, linux/amd64)

<span style="color: var(--color-teal);">$</span> voxeltrond --version
voxeltrond v1.0.0 (rust 1.82, linux/amd64)</code></pre>

  <h2>Start the daemon</h2>

  <pre><code><span style="color: var(--color-teal);">$</span> voxeltrond start
<span style="color: var(--color-lime);">✓</span> Daemon started
<span style="color: var(--color-lime);">✓</span> gRPC listening on 0.0.0.0:7443 (TLS)
<span style="color: var(--color-lime);">✓</span> Reverse proxy listening on 0.0.0.0:80 and 0.0.0.0:443
<span style="color: var(--color-lime);">✓</span> State stored at /var/lib/voxeltrond/</code></pre>

  <p>For production use, the installer creates a systemd service. Enable it:</p>

  <pre><code><span style="color: var(--color-teal);">$</span> sudo systemctl enable --now voxeltrond</code></pre>

  <h2>Connect the TUI</h2>

  <p>On your local machine (or the server itself), launch the TUI:</p>

  <pre><code><span style="color: var(--color-teal);">$</span> voxeltron
<span style="color: var(--color-lime);">✓</span> Connected to voxeltrond v1.0.0 at localhost:7443
  0 services running · uptime 0m · 2 CPUs · 2.0 GB RAM</code></pre>

  <p>If connecting from a remote machine, pass the host:</p>

  <pre><code><span style="color: var(--color-teal);">$</span> voxeltron --host my-server.example.com:7443</code></pre>

  <div class="callout tip">
    The TUI uses Vim-style keybindings. Press <code>?</code> at any time to see the help overlay.
    Press <code>q</code> to go back. Press <code>ctrl+a</code> to open the AI panel.
  </div>

  <h2>What's next?</h2>

  <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 16px; margin-top: 24px;">
    {[
      { href: '/docs/installation', emoji: '📦', title: 'Full Installation Guide', body: 'Detailed install for different platforms, from source, and post-install verification.' },
      { href: '/docs/first-deployment', emoji: '🚀', title: 'Your First Deployment', body: 'Deploy a Docker image or a GitHub repo to your server in under 5 minutes.' },
      { href: '/docs/databases', emoji: '🗄️', title: 'Databases', body: 'Provision and manage Postgres, MySQL, Redis, and MongoDB from the TUI.' },
      { href: '/docs/ai', emoji: '🤖', title: 'AI Integration', body: 'Connect the AI panel to your preferred model and let it fix your infra.' },
    ].map((card) => (
      <a
        href={card.href}
        style="
          display: block;
          padding: 20px;
          background: var(--color-surface);
          border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
          border-radius: 10px;
          text-decoration: none;
          transition: all 0.2s ease;
        "
        class="hover-card"
      >
        <div style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 8px;">{card.emoji}</div>
        <div style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--color-text); margin-bottom: 4px;">{card.title}</div>
        <div style="font-size: 0.825rem; color: var(--color-text-2); line-height: 1.5;">{card.body}</div>
      </a>
    ))}
  </div>

  <fragment slot="next">
    <a href="/docs/installation" style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; color: var(--color-teal); text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.9rem;">
      Installation →
    </a>
  </fragment>
</DocsLayout>

<style>
  .hover-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-teal-dim);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }
</style>
